text: Hisako Mori (born 4 May 1964) is a Japanese badminton player, born in Kanagawa Prefecture. She competed in women's doubles with team mate Kimiko Jinnai at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1964 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Kanagawa Prefecture Category:Japanese female badminton players Category:Olympic badminton players of Japan Category:Badminton players at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Asian Games medalists in badminton Category:Badminton players at the 1990 Asian Games Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Japan Category:Medalists at the 1990 Asian Games
